---
// BackendPhilosophy.astro
---

<section id="philosophy" class="py-32 px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto w-full text-center">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full border border-backend-border bg-backend-surface mb-4">
      <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-backend-text">
        <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
        <line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"></line>
        <line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"></line>
      </svg>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif text-white tracking-wide">
      "The best systems are the ones you never notice."
    </h2>
    
    <div class="space-y-6 text-backend-muted font-sans font-light text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-justify md:text-center">
      <p>
        Frontend development is an exercise in empathy and aesthetics. Backend engineering is an exercise in logic and anticipation. It requires thinking in edge cases, failures, and scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        A great backend is invisible. It means data is consistent, APIs respond in milliseconds, servers autoscale before traffic spikes, and security layers block threats silently. It is the quiet heartbeat of every digital experience.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
